A few months ago I had orange blossom in a dish at a restaurant in Greenpoint and promptly ordered a bottle of it to experiment with. So far I’ve made a few whipped dishes—feta, ricotta etc, and also did an olive oil loaf with orange that was to die for. So far though, a simple toast with whipped ricotta with orange blossom and toppings is still my favorite. Simple is always good. 

Whip 3/4 c whole milk ricotta, 2 tsp orange blossom water, and 1-2 tsp olive oil together in a blender or food processor. Top with fennel pollen, pistachio, honey and Maldon salt.

**Petite style tip** 

Flare, boot cut or wide leg denim with a pointed shoe will elongate your frame. Personally I’m a huge fan of the pointed toe, but any wider leg denim with a heel will do. Plus, these classics never fail. White button down, flare jeans and a sweater to go. Such a classic staple that will always be in my wardrobe. #petitefashion #petitestyle #flarejeans #interiordesign #nycapartments

Ran out of oat milk for my morning coffee so I whipped up a quick cashew milk! What you need 👇🏻

Handful raw cashews (about 1/2 cup)
About 2 cups cold water
1 tsp maple syrup 
Splash of vanilla extract
Sprinkle salt 
Hemp seeds (about 1 tsp) optional for protein! 

Add to a high powered blender and blend until very smooth. You can strain with a fine mesh strainer but I left all the goodies in. Enjoy!
